{
  "texts": [
    "The forgetting guarantees described above may not be attainable in all cases, because achieving them or computing them is unfeasible.",
    "In these cases, we can refer to empirical evaluation or auditing to provide a level of risk reduction (that is, how much the risk of the model remembering the undesired item has been reduced).",
    "These evaluations will depend on the type of forgetting request that needs to be dealt with.",
    "When requests are related to privacy or copyright protection, the difference in membership inference vulnerabilities can serve as a measure of risk reduction.",
    "If the forgetting request involves corrections of biases in the models, fairness metrics can be used."
  ]
}